text.div:
Australian and New Zealand Standard Classification of Occupations

http://www.abs.gov.au/ausstats/abs@.nsf/mf/1220.0

The Australian and New Zealand Standard Classification of Occupations (ANZSCO) provides a basis for the standardised collection, analysis and dissemination of occupation data for Australia and New Zealand. Full details can be found at http://www.abs.gov.au/ausstats/abs@.nsf/mf/1220.0. This CodeSystem resource represents version 1.2 of the standard. The structure of the classification is represented through hierarchy. Operational codes are not included as part of the classification structure and are orphan codes. The principle title designation is the default value for display and definition.
